--- Check: Prohibit Cached Authenticators After One Day ---

Check 1: SSSD Credential Cache
  SSSD: NOT CONFIGURED (no /etc/sssd/sssd.conf)

Check 2: PAM Timestamp Module
  pam_timestamp: NOT CONFIGURED

Check 3: Sudo Credential Cache
  sudo timestamp_timeout: DEFAULT (5 minutes)
  Sudo cache: well within 1-day (86400 second) requirement

Check 4: Kerberos Ticket Lifetime
  Kerberos: NOT CONFIGURED

RESULT: Cached authenticators expire well within one day.
  Sudo caches credentials for 5 minutes (default). SSSD/Kerberos
  are either not configured or have appropriate expiration.
